items.name: Japanese mascot. ゆるキャラ
items.description:
Prompt

  • No activation word, some helper words

  • girl・女性: white background, solo, 1girl, chibi, ...

  • guy・男性：white background, solo, male focus, 1boy, chibi, ...

  • animal and fruit・動物と果物: white background, solo, no humans, pokemon \(creature\), ...

Notes:

  • data is easy to find: https://chocotabi-saitama.jp/yurutama/ , https://www.homemate.co.jp/chara/ , tagged data available　。　データをアップロードしました

  • it is impossible to make a textual inversion, because the lines are too thick, the text inversion will become 'thick line, thick line, thick line' and look like pixel art　。Text Inversionは難しいです、太い線のせいで、「線、線、線、」になって、キュビスム又はピクセルアートが出ます。

  • you need the helper word 'chibi' or the humans will not converge as fast as the animals during training　。「チビ」を加えると、人間人物と動物人物は同時に収束します

  • I used helper word 'pokemon \(creature\)' because there are 100k images on Danbooru。段ボールでポケモンの画像十万枚ありまして、手伝います。「マスコット」の画像は千枚ありますし、いつもコスプレ、ぬいぐるみ、キーチェーンです。

  • I used simplified tagging for training, because if the apple character has a flower, 'no humans, apple, flower', could also mean a flower character with an apple, which changes the drawing completely。「no humans, apple, flower」は曖昧です（リンゴモチーフ、花を持つか、花モチーフ、リンゴを持つか）、だから数タッグだけを使いました。

  • Other possible helper word that have not been used: straight-on, flat_color, furry.　Still need to traina Lora to have a character with the head of a vegetable.　ほかのHelper wordも次の学習に加えられる。ですが、人物の頭は野菜・果物に代わりたい場合は、Loraは必要と思います、プロンプトだけでで出来ないと思います（試したことがありません）

  • Trained on AnyLora

Gothic interior design is characterized by grandeur, mystery, and dramatic intensity. It encompasses dark, rich color palettes, heavy fabrics, ornate furnishings, and architectural elements such as pointed arches and intricate stonework. Her hair can be difficult to get right. In her nun outfit, no additional hair prompt is necessary. Without her nun outfit, you can add pigtails to the prompt or negative prompt if you want pigtails or straight hair, respectively.

items.name: Greek style interior design
items.description:
Only for SD 2.1

Greek style interior design embodies the spirit of Ancient Greece with an emphasis on simplicity, functionality, and harmony. The color palette is typically dominated by white, contrasted with blues or earthy tones. The use of natural light is key, often enhanced with open floor plans. Furnishings are usually straightforward and functional, often made from stone or wood. Decorative accents might include pottery, sculptures, or olive branches. Key architectural elements include columns, mosaics, and marble. Overall, Greek style seeks to create a fresh, airy, and tranquil environment that echoes the timeless beauty of the Mediterranean.

items.name: Indonesian style interior design
items.description:
Only for SD 2.1

Indonesian style interior design is characterized by the use of traditional crafts, natural materials, and a rich blend of Asian influences. It reflects the cultural diversity of the Indonesian archipelago, with elements from Javanese, Balinese, and other regional styles.

The color palette tends to be warm, with earthy tones and vibrant accents. Materials like teak, bamboo, rattan, and batik fabrics are often used, providing a connection to the natural environment.

Furniture is typically substantial and ornately carved, while decor often includes traditional masks, sculptures, and textile arts. Intricate wooden details and tropical plants further enhance the aesthetic.

Overall, Indonesian style creates a peaceful, welcoming ambiance, balancing elegance and exotic charm with an appreciation for natural beauty and craftsmanship.
